{"id":"hep-th/9306060","submitter":"Costas Efthimiou","authors":"Costas John Efthimiou and Donald Spector","title":"Separation of Variables and Exactly Soluble Time-Dependent Potentials in\n  Quantum Mechanics","comments":"REVTEX, 30 pages, CLNS-93/1188, HWS-9313","journal-ref":"Phys.Rev. A48 (1993) 2301","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th","license":null,"abstract":"  We use separation of variables as a tool to identify and to analyze exactly\nsoluble time-dependent quantum mechanical potentials. By considering the most\ngeneral possible time-dependent re-definition of the spatial coordinate, as\nwell as general transformations on the wavefunctions, we show that separation\nof variables applies and exact solubility occurs only in a very restricted\nclass of time-dependent models. We consider the formal structure underlying our\nfindings, and the relationship between our results and other work on\ntime-dependent potentials. As an application of our methods, we apply our\nresults to the calculations of propagators.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 13 Jun 1993 21:36:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
